        <p>
          *Article 16 ensures that everyone has an equal chance to compete for
          government jobs, regardless of their background, thereby promoting
          fairness and justice.
        </p>
        <p>
          * It protects against discrimination based on religion, race, caste,
          sex, and other irrelevant factors, ensuring that employment decisions
          are based on merit rather than bias.
        </p>
        <p>
          * By allowing reservations, Article 16 promotes the inclusion of
          underrepresented communities in public employment. This helps to
          correct historical injustices and ensures that disadvantaged groups
          have equal opportunities to work in government jobs
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
