        <p>
          *Article 17 declares that "untouchability" is abolished and its
          practice in any form is forbidden. This means that no one can
          discriminate against anyone else by treating them as "untouchable."
        </p>
        <p>
          * Article 17 prohibits anyone from enforcing or encouraging the
          practice of untouchability. Any action or behavior that discriminates
          against individuals based on this outdated and discriminatory practice
          is illegal.
        </p>
        <p>
          * Article 17 abolishes the practice of "untouchability" in India and
          forbids anyone from discriminating against others based on this
          practice. It ensures that all citizens, regardless of their caste or
          background, are treated equally and with dignity. The article also
          provides for legal action and punishment against those who practice or
          promote untouchability, making it a powerful tool for achieving social
          justice and equality.
        </p>
